  "summary": "After visiting a friend who is opening an auto repair shop, Bobby Jones catches the 11:30 train from Paddington Station to return home. He narrowly boards a first-class carriage just as it departs, finding the only other passenger to be Frankie (Miss Francis DeWinter). The two share a history as childhood acquaintances through their families, the Joneses and the DeWinters, though they have grown apart due to social differences and the formality of the Jones family.\n\nDuring the journey, Frankie expresses her exhaustion with life in the countryside and recounts a recent, underwhelming social outing. Their conversation shifts to a news report regarding a \"Fatal Accident in Sea Fog.\" Frankie reveals she read about the man who fell off a cliff, whom Bobby and his father, Thomas, had discovered. The newspaper identifies the deceased as Alexander Prichard, a man who had recently returned from Siam. Bobby notes that Prichard was not dead when they found him but died fifteen minutes later.\n\nAs they discuss the upcoming inquest in Marigold, Bobby mentions his friend Budge Bidden. Through a series of shared childhood memories regarding Budge's stuttering and past failures—including a bankrupt chicken farm and a brief stint at a stock brokerage—Frankie realizes she knows him, confirming his history of being sent to Australia before returning to England.",
